# <type>(<scope>): <subject>  (50 chars max)
#
# <body>  (72 chars per line, what & why, not how)
#
# <footer>  (refs, breaking changes, co-authors)
#
# Types autorises (conventional commits) :
#   feat     — nouvelle fonctionnalite
#   fix      — correction de bug
#   refactor — refacto sans changement comportement
#   docs     — documentation seulement
#   chore    — outillage, deps, configs (pas de code prod)
#   test     — ajout/correction de tests
#   perf     — amelioration performance
#   style    — formatage, semicolons (pas logique)
#   ci       — CI/CD
#   build    — build system, deps releases
#
# Scopes courants :
#   api, web, infra, ci, docs, deps, security, pec, cosium, ...
#
# Exemples :
#   feat(pec): batch submission endpoint
#   fix(web): scroll lock on dialog open
#   refactor(api): split reconciliation_service in 3 files
#   chore(ci): add bandit security scan
#
# Pour activer ce template :
#   git config commit.template .gitmessage
